  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Purchasing Executive - [ST]",
  "description": "<h2><strong>Purchase Executive</strong></h2><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p>Coordinate with project teams to consolidate purchase needs and delivery timelines</p></li><li><p>Interpret BQ, datasheets, and technical specifications to ensure material compliance</p></li><li><p>Source ELV and electrical materials from local and China suppliers</p></li><li><p>Review and compare supplier quotations, pricing, and lead times</p></li><li><p>Negotiate pricing, payment terms, and delivery schedules</p></li><li><p>Issue POs/DOs and coordinate deliveries to site or warehouse</p></li><li><p>Handle supplier issues, returns, replacements, and warranty claims</p></li><li><p>Maintain proper procurement documentation and supplier records</p></li><li><p>Monitor purchase costs against BQ/quotation budgets</p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li><p>Diploma or equivalent in Procurement, Engineering, or related field</p></li><li><p>2–4 years of purchasing/procurement experience, preferably in ELV or electrical materials</p></li><li><p>Able to read and understand basic technical specifications and BQ</p></li><li><p>Strong negotiation and coordination skills</p></li><li><p>Proficient in ERP systems and Microsoft Excel</p></li><li><p><strong>Able to communicate in Mandarin to liaise with China suppliers</strong><br /></p><p>We appreciate your interest and look forward to reviewing your application. Due to high application volume, only shortlisted candidates will be contacted — thank you for your understanding!</p><p></p><p>WeCruit Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0270</p><p>EA Personnel: Tan Soon Hock (Steven) | Registration No. R1109889</p></li></ul>",
